1.title: Mark Landon Smith/Serrano-Torres/Keith Burmylo
1.plot: We launch Season 6 of Later with Jason Suel with a real doozy of a show. We sit down with Mark Landon Smith, Northwest Arkansas agent to the stars and Executive Director of Arts Live Theatre; Food from Keith Burmylo of Bocca Italian Eatery; And, music from Christian Serrano-Torres. Plus, EVERYTHING else you've come to love about our show. We'll see you Later!"

2.title: Monica Jannati/Stephen Pigman/Anthony Oseguera
2.plot: We're back with another fabulous lineup. Monica Jannati joins us to chat about an INK-tastic event coming to Fayetteville. PLUS food from Anthony Oseguera and Music from Stephen Pigman. Thanks for joining us now and be sure to join us again, Later.

3.title: Hazel Hernandez & Russell Sharman/Foggy Bobcat/Case Dighero
3.plot: Calling all movie buffs: We sit down and chat with Russell and Hazel about the Fayetteville Film Fest, and Chef Case Dighero, Bo and Jason get cozy while discussing the best foods to pop while movie-watching AND musical guest Foggy Bobcat claws their way onto the show. Hope to see you again - Later.

4.title: Raymond House/The Downtown Livewires/Chef Case Dighero
4.plot: Fall and football go hand in hand. We sit down with former Razorback football star Raymond House to chat about what's happening on the gridiron, music by the Downtown Livewires, AND we take your tailgate cuisine up a notch as Chef Case takes on the grill. Cheer now; Victories Later.

5.title: Max Avery/Beer & Hymns/Chef Haley O'Brien
5.plot: Max Avery joins us to talk about upcoming things happening in the River Valley. Plus, we hear from local group "Beer and Hymns," and Chef Haley O'Brien drops by with beer cheese - We've got fun on tap - Later.

6.title: Professor Gallico & Fernando/Jason Willems/Route 358
6.plot: Abracadabra - Alakazam, A magician as a guest would be our Jam. So, we have Dr. Anton Gallico and the Amazing Fernando joining us, music from Route 358 and we mix up something special with Jason Willems. Poof. All the fun happens - Later.

7.title: Tyrone Washington/Up Beat/Steven Brooks
7.plot: It's that time of year; time for our Halloween episode. Dr. Tyrone Washington is back with some spooky science tricks. We even have a bed of nails. And food from one of our favorite chefs, Steven Brooks. Get spooky with us - Later.

8.title: Lynette Washington/Lyrique Quintette/Jovan Williams
8.plot: Have you ever wondered how to throw a shot-put? We sit down with Lynette Washington to talk sports and how to keep the kiddos active. We have food from Chef Jovan Williams, music from Lyirque Quintette and Turbo Dan is back and more extreme than ever - Have fun with us, Later.

9.title: Al Bell/The Downtown Livewires/Steven Brooks
9.plot: Al Bell joins us to talk about his journey through the music scene and what's he's doing here in Northwest Arkansas. Musical guests are The Downtown Livewires and there's food from Chef Steven Brooks who also plays the drums. We're staying musically sound - Later.

10.title: Jenn Cozens/Brian Pounds/The Holler
10.plot: We are joined by Mover and Shaker Jenn Cozens, music from Brian Pounds AND we turned Chef Case Dighero loose on Bentonville's new hot-spot, The Holler. Join us as we get game-y - Later.

11.title: Dylan Turk/Galactech Raiders/Tang's Asian Market
11.plot: It's all of the things we love and in one dynamic episode. We hear from Northwest Arkansas influence, Dylan Turk. We visit Tang's Asian Market with Chef Case, plus Jason, Bo and Dan don their police officer attire for another installment of "Up Beat." Tune in LATER.

12.title: Sarah Beth Pfeifer/Elayne's Dance/Harvest Moon Pies
12.plot: Join us for an episode filmed in front of a live audience at Walton Arts Center. Featuring Broadway actor Sarah Beth Pfeifer, food from Harvest Moon Pies, a swing dance lesson from Elayne's Dance and wait - is that Turbo Dan dressed as a cat? You don't want to miss this, LATER.

13.title: Trike Theatre/Phunbags/Philip Haughey/Austin Dean Ashford
13.plot: In front of a live audience at Walton Arts Center, we feature actors from Trike Theatre's production of 'Go Dog Go,' Philip Haughey mixes drinks, Austin Dean Ashford strums some chords and Phunbags cracks us up. We'll see you, LATER.

14.title: Dayton Castleman/The Downtown Livewires/Matthew Cooper
14.plot: We're back with a brand new episode featuring artist Dayton Castleman, the music of Roger Thomas and the Downtown Livewires and food from Chef Matthew Cooper of The Preacher's Son. ALL THE THINGS are happening - Later!"

15.title: Bianca Montoya/Something Better/Maudie Schmitt
15.plot: We talk with NWA mover and shaker Bianca Montoya, music from the band 'Something Better,' food from Chef Maudie Schmitt and the boys are back in BLUE. - We'll see you - Later.

1.title: Coleman Clark/Kayleigh Calaway/Case Dighero
1.plot: Fayetteville native and New York based theatre professional Coleman Clark joins us in studio. Food from the multi-talented Case Dighero and music from Kayleigh Calaway.

2.title: Jerrmy Gawthrop & Bryan Hembree/Joe Purdy/William Lyle
2.plot: Jason sits down with Fayetteville Roots Festival organizers Bryan Hembree and Jerrmy Gawthrop. Music from Roots Fest performer, Joe Purdy. And, Chef Bill Lyle is back in the kitchen.

3.title: Blake Elder & Chase Goforth/The Vine Brothers/Heather Artripe
3.plot: We talk to filmmakers Chase Goforth and Blake Elder about the upcoming Fayetteville Film Fest, Music from The Vine Brothers, food from Chef Heather Artripe of Ozark Natural Foods, and some explosive fun with the Galactech Raiders.

4.title: August Recap
4.plot: Later with Jason Suel recaps our August episodes AND we are joined by a panel of experts...special guests, Warren Rosenaur, Melissa Hall, and Alex Caprariello - an episode you don't want to miss.

5.title: Robert Ford & Austin Ashford/Opal Agafia/Julie Sill
5.plot: We have Robert Ford and Austin Ashford from Theatre Squared, food from Julie Sill of HogHaus Brewing, and music from Opal Agafia and the Sweet Nothings.

6.title: Helena Gadison/Maud Crawford/Amanda Robinson
6.plot: We have Helena Gadison here to talk about how to improve your personal brand, Fried Pies with Amanda Robinson of Harvest Moon Pies and Music from Maud Crawford. It's all here on 'Later!'

7.title: Northwest Arkansas Hot Spot Recap
7.plot: There is so much happening in Northwest Arkansas. Bo and Jason go galavanting around NWA checking out some new and some familiar hot spots. Also, Jonald Farfe - Also, Galactech Raiders - Ahhh. You don't want to miss it.

8.title: Liz Atwell/Witchsister/Tammy Varney & Brandon Bullette
8.plot: Boo. Join our hauntingly talented cast as we interview Liz Atwell from the Botanical Garden of the Ozarks, Music from Witchsister AND an edible collaboration between Tammy Varney and Brandon Bullette, Get spooked. - on 'Later.'

9.title: Jason Carney/Darren Ray/Matthew Cooper
9.plot: We're back with guest Jason Carney talking about his non-profit 2nd Milk. Food from Chef Matthew Cooper of the Preacher's Son - Yum. AND our puppets are back with musical guest Darren Ray in an episode you DON'T want to miss.

10.title: Stace Treat/Fourscore/Sarah Chase
10.plot: We've crafted something special in collaboration with Crystal Bridges Museum of American Art. We've got Stace Treat talking about the Stuart Davis exhibition and Chef Sarah Chase from Eleven Restaurant. PLUS a jazz quartet to boot.

11.title: Chris Goddard/Smokey & The Mirror/Steven Brooks
11.plot: A we prepare for Thanksgiving, here are a few of the things we're thankful for: Chris Goddard from Goddard Design Group; A fresh twist on a traditional Thanksgiving dessert from Chef Steven Brooks; Music by Smokey and the Mirror and MORE.

12.title: Mindy Yates/Handmade Moments/Anna & Sam Russell
12.plot: Looking to shed a few pounds after an Thanksgiving? Then DO NOT watch Later with Jason Suel because with Sam and Anna Russell from The Buttered Biscuit stopping by show off their biscuits. We sit down with thrifty interior designer Mindy Yates; AND there's music by Handmade Moments.

13.title: New Year Special: Part 1
13.plot: It's Part 1 of our New Year Special featuring Emily Tomlinson, food from Chef Case Dighero, Music from Caleb Conrad, and the hilarity of Phunbags Comedy Improv. Happy New Year from 'Later!'

14.title: New Year Special: Part 2
14.plot: It's Part 2 of our New Year Special. Chef Case Dighero and Caleb Conrad will still be here PLUS a special appearance from Instagrampaw and - wait, is that? Yep, a Live Gorilla - We'll see you, 'Later!'

15.title: Kassie Misiewicz & Paul Savas/Photosphere/Jon Allen
15.plot: Paul and Kassie roll in to talk about Trike Theatre. We make the world's best cup of coffee with Onyx Coffee Lab's Jon Allen AND music from Photosphere - We'll see you 'Later!'

16.title: Amy Robinson/Brick Fields/Rob Nelson
16.plot: Jason and Bo interview Amy Robinson from Tribe of Women, there's food from Chef Rob Nelson from Tusk and Trotter, with music from Brick Fields and MORE. DVR the show, so you can watch it now and Later.

17.title: Jennica & Ryan Schwartzman/Common Roots/Jason Paul
17.plot: Jason sits down with the family filmmaking team of Ryan and Jennica Schwartzman, music from Common Roots, food from Heirloom's Chef Jason Paul and a few shenanigans to boot. All here, on 'Later!'

18.title: Heidi Tankersley/Grace Pettis/Shayla Holder
18.plot: Relationship triangles, chocolate, happy places, what's not to LOVE!?. Join us as Jason and Bo chat with teen fiction author, Heidi Tankersley, music from Grace Pettis, and chocolate from Conscious Coco's Shayla Holder - it's so good, you'll want some now AND 'Later!'

19.title: Damon Henke & Lilah Stiger/Red Oak Ruse/Michael Robertshaw
19.plot: Damon and Lilah slip down from Eureka Springs. Chef Michael Robertshaw drops by to make us something that's certainly not Fal-awful. And we have the music of Red Oak Ruse.

20.title: Graham Cobb/DocFell & Co./Dennis Arrington
20.plot: Our 60th episode. We celebrate with an all-star lineup. Graham Cobb sits down to talk all things Bentonville. There's music from DocFell and Company. And, Chef Dennis Arrington brings us the luck of the Irish with his cuisine. Let's celebrate - 'Later!'

21.title: Joey Lauren Adams/Jasper Logan/Rafael Rios
21.plot: Joey Lauren Adams is here. Plus musical guest Jasper Logan. AND we're premiering our first 'Case in the Joint' segment. That's right Chef Case is on the loose. We can't wait to see you 'Later!'

22.title: Betsy & Kevin Bernier/Cameron Johnson/Vince Pianalto
22.plot: We're talking about the Power of Music festival with Betsy and Kevin and food from Chef Vince Pianalto. Speaking of music having power, we spotlight a musician that's not to be missed: Cameron Johnson - Join us for the POWER, 'Later!'

23.title: Lauren Marquette/ilyAIMY/Markham & Fitz
23.plot: Lauren Marquette from Susan Komen Ozark joins us, as well as music from ilyAIMY. PLUS Chef Case Dighero is back to Case the Joint. It's all happening, 'Later!'

24.title: Debra Capps/Shannon Wurst/Matthew McClure
24.plot: Debra Capps is in-studio to chat with us about the Bentonville Film Festival. Everyone's BFF Shannon Wurst performs for us AND food from James Beard award semi-finalist, Chef Matthew McClure!!. We'll see you 'Later!'

25.title: Amanda Reed/Dr. Tyrone Washington/Rafael Rios
25.plot: We're THRILLED to welcome Amanda Reed to the studio to talk about trends in this year's wedding season. PLUS Rafael Rios from Yeyo's Mexican Grill ROCKS some cuisine AND Dr. Tyrone Washington is here with some EXPLOSIVE fun. Check it out, 'Later!'

26.title: Lioneld Jordan/Chris Goering/Taco Tour
26.plot: Fayetteville Mayor, Lioneld Jordan joins us next time. What fun. Chef Case Dighero takes us on the Taco Tour of Springdale AND we go camping in the Ozarks - All here, on 'Later!'

27.title: Dylan Turk/Lesley Reynaga/William McCormick
27.plot: We have a special episode of Later. Filmed in front of a live audience at Crystal Bridges Museum of American Art, we welcome Cynthia Post Hunt, Dylan Turk, Music from Lesly Reynaga, food from Chef William McCormick and MORE - we'll talk all things ART - Later.

28.title: Jennifer Wilson/Makin Loaf/Steven Idlet
28.plot: This time on Later with Jason Suel, we chat with Jennifer Wilson about Walton Arts Center's Artosphere Festival, we'll also mix-up a summer delight with Steven Idlet while we listen to the sounds of Sarah Loethen. Join us, Later.

29.title: Marty Shutter/Amy Andrews/Brent Hale
29.plot: A talented performer in his own right, we've got Ozark Beer Company's Marty Shutter joining us as; well as food from Mr. Big Sexy Food himself, Chef Brent Hale. Annndd, Baltimore-based singer, songwriter Amy Andrews reminds us that there truly is no place like home. We'll see you Later.

30.title: 4th of July Special
30.plot: Feeling independent? It's our 4th of July Extravaganza. We are joined by millennial expert Chelsey Herrold. PLUS our First Annual RIB cook-off featuring 2 area chefs and judged by "Experience Fayetteville's" Molly Rawn and Fayetteville's Mayor Lioneld Jordan. Let's celebrate our Independence together - Later.

31.title: Crescent Dragonwagon/The Honey Dewdrops/Emily Lawson
31.plot: It's time for the FAYETTEVILLE ROOTS FESTIVAL. We're joined by plenty of folks from this year's fest including Jerrmy Gawthrop - Crescent Dragonwagon - Pink House Alchemy's Emily Lawson AND we premiere a new music video from Root Fest performers 'The Honey Dew Drops.' I wish we could watch it now instead of - Later.

32.title: Finale
32.plot: And now it's time to say goodbye to all of Season 5. Join Jason Suel and Jaclyn House as they bid farewell to everything that made Season 5 so great. Food, Music, Comedy, Personalities and Fun. It's a special Season Ending episode - but don't worry, we'll be back for Season 6 - Later.

imdb.plot outline: 'Later with Jason Suel' is a late-night talk/variety show hosted by Jason Suel. The show currently runs on Northwest Arkansas' Fox Affiliate, Fox 24. Portions of the show are also available on YouTube and Fayetteville Public Television. Along with Jason, the show stars a house band consisting of Jason Reddecliff, Owen McClung, and Charlie Platt and a featured sidekick, Bo Counts.
